Material Information Summary (Herberton Project VTEM Survey Results)

  • Exploration Results:
  • Strong EM anomalies identified at Orient Project, suggesting potential extensions of known silver-indium mineralization.
  • New anomalies at Deadman Creek (northern extension of Orient System) indicate possible sulphide mineralization.

  • Exploration suggests Orient mineral system larger than previously known, with both East and West zones open for expansion.

  • Next Steps:

  • Modeling of VTEM anomalies (prioritizing Orient area) to rank targets for drill testing (expected mid-to-late July 2025).

  • Fieldwork (mapping/sampling) at Deadman Creek and other anomalies.

  • Funding:

  • Received AUD $230,375 from Queensland Government’s Collaborative Exploration Initiative (CEI) for the VTEM survey.

  • Exploration Target:

  • Orient Project global target: 32–42 Mt @ 110–124 g/t Ag Eq. (80 g/t cutoff).

No capital raising, trading halt, or financial adjustments identified.

Announcement Type: Strategic Partnership (MoU)

  • Potential Rio Tinto funding for optimization test work and pilot/demonstration plant design (Argentina).

- Positive catalyst for NMT’s lithium technology commercialization, given Rio Tinto’s Tier-1 lithium assets and funding potential.
- Risks: MoU is non-binding; no guarantee of formal agreement.

Projects Update Summary – Alpha HPA Limited (ASX: A4N)

Stage 2 HPA Project (Expansion)

  • Civil works commenced with contractor mobilisation and IFC drawings issued.
  • Offsite fabrication underway for long-lead equipment (solvent extraction modules, tanks).
  • LOI coverage at 63% of Stage 2 production capacity, with 5 additional LOIs under negotiation.

Product Demand & Sales

  • Semiconductor sector driving growth: 18 new potential customers added this quarter; AI/data center demand cited.
  • >360 test/sales orders since May 2024; recent orders include bespoke HPA/ATH powders (100–1,500kg lots).
  • Ultra-high density HPA tablets (3.9g/cm³) developed for semiconductor machinery parts; samples sent for qualification.

Stage 1 Operations

  • Current production:
  • 900kg/day ultra-pure Al-Nitrate (5N).
  • 400kg/week ATH powder (4N7).
  • 300kg/week HPA tablets (5N).
  • Stage 1 fully booked until 30 June 2025; demand exceeds capacity.

Alpha Sapphire (Synthetic Sapphire)

  • First 200mm wafer sales to semiconductor OEM for GaN-on-sapphire qualification.
  • Conditional agreement for 2 tonnes of sapphire boules in 2025; optics customer seeks >100% of 2026 output.
  • Quality improvements: Reduced defects, contamination, and enhanced yield.

Key Catalyst

  • Stage 2 progress (critical path: engineering/fabrication) and LOI conversions to binding contracts.
